item.title: RANDOM PASS GENERATOR by APS!
item.dc:creator: @Ron Ron
item.description:
@Ron wrote:

I formatted the code for you. 

// Random Pass Generator by Aps

Program RandomPass;

Var a : Integer;
    StartTime : Integer;

Begin
  StartTime := GetTickCount;
  If(IsFKeydown(9))Then
  Begin
    Repeat
      a := 1 + Random(9999999);
      a := a * 1;
      a := a + 1 + Random(999999);
      Wait(1 + Random(100));
      WriteLn(IntToStr(a));
    Until(GetTickCount - StartTime > 5000);
    WriteLn('DING!');
  End;
End.

item.dc:creator: @Weibs Weibs
item.description:
@Weibs wrote:

Ok, first of all, because there is no repeat around the if(isFKey… the script will check for the FKey right away, and only once. There for the script will start and stop right away. Just add a Repeat Until(false); around the if statement, and add a break; after the then so the script breaks out of the loop when the FKey has been pressed down.

Also, doesn’t this just generate random numbers?

But keep up on the script making

-Weibs.
